pull_request.title: Add renewal cost logic to DomainPricingLogic
pull_request.body: The purpose of this PR is to add renewal support for anchor tenants and internal registrations in the renew flow. This will be used in `ExpandRecurringBillingEventsAction` ([PR#1609](https://github.com/google/nomulus/pull/1609)), `DomainRenewFlow` ([PR#1592](https://github.com/google/nomulus/pull/1592)), and `DomainFlowUtil` ([PR#1637](https://github.com/google/nomulus/pull/1637)). While I was working on this PR, I found out that there's no test file for `DomainPricingLogic.java` - Most of the logic files are wrappers but `DomainPricingLogic` contains calculations of different kinds of prices such as `renew` and `transfer`. I added test cases for `getRenewPrice()` and there should be cases for other calculation methods as well. I opened a bug to track that. In order to create an instance of `DomainPricingLogic`, the constructor of `DomainPricingCustomLogic` needs to be made public. --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/google/nomulus/1610)

pull_request.title: Make Caffeine cache loading work in non-GAE thread
pull_request.body: Caffeine cache loading happens asynchronously in a different thread than the main app engine thread. When a VKey is created in that thread, it tries to ascertain that the current thread is an GAE thread and fails. In this PR we introduce a `MasqueradedCacheLoader` abstract class that overrides the `reload` function, which runs in the background thread to refresh the cache on demand, in order to trick Ofy into thinking that it runs in an GAE thread. --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/google/nomulus/1634)

pull_request.title: Make Caffeine cache loading work in non-GAE thread
pull_request.body: Caffeine cache loading happens asynchronously in a different thread than the main app engine thread. When a VKey is created in that thread, it tries to ascertain that the current thread is an GAE thread and fails. In this PR we introduce a `MasqueradedCacheLoader` abstract class that overrides the `reload` function, which runs in the background thread to refresh the cache on demand, in order to trick Ofy into thinking that it runs in an GAE thread. --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/google/nomulus/1634)
